# Copy to ".env" (or ".env.local") and restart `npm run dev`.
#
# --- Catalog API (required for products/categories on the storefront) ---
# Must point at the *admin* deployment’s public API for ONE store — same DB the admin UI uses.
# Shape (no trailing slash): https://<your-admin-domain>/api/<storeId>
# The <storeId> is the UUID in the admin URL path, e.g. opening Categories at
#   https://admin.example.com/ea40601b-1a0f-4e7b-a373-dc4987d87b47/categories
# means NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://admin.example.com/api/ea40601b-1a0f-4e7b-a373-dc4987d87b47
# Wrong storeId or missing variable → empty storefront; admin can still show another store.
# On Vercel: set for Production (and Preview if you use preview URLs), then redeploy — NEXT_PUBLIC_* is baked in at build.
# Do not wrap the value in quotes in the Vercel UI (or strip them); stray quotes break fetch URLs.

# --- AI provider (optional; default is OpenAI) ---
# openai  → OPENAI_API_KEY (default)
# openrouter → OPENROUTER_API_KEY, base URL https://openrouter.ai/api/v1 (set in code)
#AI_PROVIDER=openai

# Model id (optional). OpenAI default: gpt-4o-mini. OpenRouter default: openai/gpt-4o-mini
#AI_MODEL=

# --- OpenAI (default provider) ---
# https://platform.openai.com/api-keys — billing: https://platform.openai.com/account/billing
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- OpenRouter (when AI_PROVIDER=openrouter) ---
# https://openrouter.ai/keys
#OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# Optional but recommended for OpenRouter rankings / attribution:
#OPENROUTER_HTTP_REFERER=https://your-site.example
#OPENROUTER_APP_TITLE=My Store

NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=
